cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with Device-to-Device (D2D) communications in LTE-A networks. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the optimization of resource allocation and scheduling. It may also fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it formulates a general problem for joint per-user mode selection, connection activation, and resource scheduling. Furthermore, it could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with the transmission of multimedia content through D2D communications. Lastly, it could belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it may discuss the security implications of D2D communications.
